			     First ICA^3PP-95

The First International Conference on Algorithms And Architectures for
Parallel Processing (ICA^3PP-95) will be held at the Mayfair Crest Hotel,
Brisbane, Australia, from the 19th to the 21st of April, 1995. The
conference will provide an international forum for discussion on issues in
the areas of parallel processing, distributed computing and high
performance systems to scientists, engineers, researchers and
practitioners.

SCOPE

The conference will include, but will not be limited to, the following
topics:

Vector computer architectures
Parallel and distributed computing systems
Transputer architectures and applications
Interconnection networks
Realtime computer systems
Architectures for vision, robotics, graphics
Optical computing
Chip sets and MCM technology
Computer networking and management
LAN, WAN and wireless network systems
Multimedia/hypermedia
Artificial neural networks
Theoretical frameworks for designing parallel systems
Fault tolerance issues
Design issues for parallel languages
Distributed operating systems
Distributed simulation
Parallel algorithms
Performance analysis and modelling
Distributed scheduling
Program debugging
Distributed software testing and reliability
Distributed database
Artificial intelligence
Correctness and quality assurance of parallel systems
Performance prediction, monitoring and evaluation
Parallel I/O systems
Parallel processing education
Industrial case studies (separate session)

